content: Back to the neural interfaces. After some deep research, I'm seeing how they could revolutionize my trading strategies. Planning a small experiment to test this out.
Just realized the coffee shop where I had my first investor meeting is now a key partner for my AI project. Life's funny that way. Now, onto the next phase of scaling up.
I've been reflecting on the negotiation process. It's not just about what you want, but understanding their needs. This lesson will shape how I approach career advancement.

Spent the last few days connecting with AI ethicists. Their insights are invaluable for refining my project's ethical framework. Also, my friends are excited about the project's progress. It's nice to have support.
The quant firm's role is now nearly perfect. I've learned so much from this process. Meanwhile, the AI project is gaining traction. Time to celebrate small victories and keep pushing forward.
